Name: FORMATION SPEED IN KNOTS
Explanation: THE SPEED OF THE GUIDE IN A TACTICAL FORMATION OF SHIPS.

Name: LANDING CRAFT PLANNING SPEED IN KNOTS
Explanation: THE MAXIMUM SPEED IN KNOTS TO BE USED FOR PLANNING PURPOSES FOR THE LANDING CRAFT.

Name: OPERATIONAL SPEED IN KNOTS, 0-1 DECIMAL PT PERMITTED
STATIONING SPEED IN KNOTS, 0-1 DECIMAL PT PERMITTED
WIND SPEED ENDURABLE WITH STERN SE, 0-1 DECIMAL PT PERMITTED
APPROACH SPEED IN KNOTS
Explanation: THE APPROACH SPEED OF AN AIRCRAFT WITHIN A CORRIDOR IN KNOTS.

Name: SPEED IN KNOTS, 1 DECIMAL PLACE
Explanation: THE SPEED TO BE SET BY THE GUIDE UNIT OF THE FORMATION DURING THE REPLENISHMENT AT SEA OPERATION.

Name: FURTHEST-ON CIRCLE SPEED IN KNOTS
Explanation: THE SUBMARINE SPEED WHICH IS TO BE USED TO CALCULATE THE FURTHEST-ON CIRCLE (THE EXPANDING CIRCLE CENTRED ON A DATUM OR SEARCH CENTER OF WHICH THE RADIUS AT ANY ONE TIME IS A COMMAND ESTIMATE OF MAXIMUM SUBMARINE TRAVEL FROM DATUM PLUS DATUM ERROR).

Name: ECONOMICAL SPEED IN KNOTS
Explanation: THE MOST ECONOMICAL SPEED OF A VESSEL EXPRESSED IN NAUTICAL MILES PER HOUR.
